<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" box="[151,619,726,751]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,619,726,751]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="Perez, 1890" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1890" box="[151,619,726,751]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Bombus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="flavidus" subSpecies="lutescens">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,619,726,751]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,457,726,751]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Bombus flavidus lutescens</emphasis>
(Pérez, 1890)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
It is spread mainly in the Pyrenees (Ornosa &amp; Torres 2009), although there is a quote from the Cantabrian Range (
<bibRefCitation author="Obeso" box="[237,377,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" refString="Obeso, J. R. (1992) Geographic distribution and community structure of bumblebees in the Northern Iberian Peninsula. Oecologia, 89, 244 - 252." type="journal article" year="1992">Obeso 1992</bibRefCitation>
). It has an orophilous tendency (
<figureCitation box="[742,810,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1517,1539]" captionTargetBox="[152,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1437,877,1496]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution (in meters) range of the bumblebee species and subspecies observed in contemporary samplings (grey rectangles) in the Pyrenees compared with the known altitude distribution (black bars) from historical data." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322695/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), between 
<date box="[932,1098,798,823]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" value="1800" valueMax="2520">
1800 and 
<quantity box="[1042,1098,798,823]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.52" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="2520.0">2520</quantity>
</date>
m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,726,967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">
The last samples (
<figureCitation box="[358,427,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1619,1641]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,1027,1590]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,1020,1596]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing historical locations (●) and recent records (*) of Bombus flavidus lutescens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/322692/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) were collected in a wet alpine pasture in a peatland in the upper limit of a fir-pine area with 
<taxonomicName box="[207,326,870,895]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[207,326,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Abies alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[340,514,870,895]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis box="[340,514,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Pinus sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. and 
<taxonomicName box="[599,768,871,894]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uncinata">
<emphasis box="[599,768,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Pinus uncinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with scattered patches of creeping juniper scrub, cranberry and heather, among others, also on 
<taxonomicName box="[546,770,906,931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="myrtillus">
<emphasis box="[546,770,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Vaccinium myrtillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[824,1031,906,931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratense">
<emphasis box="[824,1031,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="55">Trifolium pratense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at 
<quantity box="[1066,1154,907,931]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.02" pageId="14" pageNumber="55" unit="m" value="2020.0">2020 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
